. Research and Development takes place in Cape Town, South Africa and production is based predominantly in China.Leatt has warehouses and a distribution office in California for the North American Market as well as a world-wide network of distributors.Learn more about the Company Leatt HistoryThe Leatt story began in 2001 when Dr. Christopher Leatt witnessed the death of a fellow motorcycle rider the weekend after his son, Matthew, began riding.Dr Leatt began research and development of a device almost immediately, driven by a passion to protect not only his son, but all riders from the effects of catastrophic neck injuries. His first patents were filed in 2003.Learn more Investor QueriesDresner Allen Caron Michael Mason Email Michael Mason (212) 691-8087Latest FinancialsLeatt Corporation First Quarter 2017 Form 10-Qview PDF | download XBRLRELEASED: 12 May 2017Leatt Corporation 2016 10-K Annual Reportview PDF | download XBRLRELEASED: 29 Mar 2017Leatt Corporation Third Quarter 2016 Form 10-Qview PDF | download XBRLRELEASED: 10 Nov 2016VIEW ALL Filings / Financials    NavigationThe CompanyHomeCompany ProfileMeet the TeamMission and StrategyLeatt HistoryCode of EthicsLeatt ProtectivesThe Leatt BlogLeatt TestimonialsInvestor InfoFilings / FinancialsStock QuotesInvestor RelationsShareholder PresentationShareholder FAQContact UsShareholder Updates: Email Sign-Up  Notices & Disclaimers | © Copyright Leatt Corporation 2008 - 2017 | Design by kri8it.com    Contact informationResident Agent: PMB# 334 2215-B Renaissance Drive Las Vegas NV 89119USA Distribution Office: Two Eleven Distribution LLC 26475 Summit Circle, Santa Clarita, CA 91350Office: 661-287-9258 Toll Free: 800-691-3314 Fax: 661-287-9688Head Office: 12 Kiepersol Crescent Atlas Gardens Durbanville, 7550Tel: +27 21 557 7257 Fax: +27 21 557 7381 Email: investor-info@leatt.com Shareholder communication procedure: The Board of Directors has established a procedure that enables stockholders to communicate in writing wit