 Leatt History - Leatt Corporation             Leatt Corporation DESIGNERS, DEVELOPERS AND MARKETERS OF INNOVATIVE PROTECTIVE GEAR for sportsLeatt CorporationDESIGNERS, DEVELOPERS AND MARKETERS OF INNOVATIVE PROTECTIVE GEAR for sports       Leatt History The Leatt story began in 2001 when Dr. Christopher Leatt witnessed the death of a fellow motorcycle rider the weekend after his son, Matthew, began riding.Dr Leatt began research and development of a device almost immediately, driven by a passion to protect not only his son, but all riders from the effects of catastrophic neck injuries. His first patents were filed in 2003. The revolutionary Leatt-Brace® was developed in Cape Town, South Africa and tested by BMW engineers at their facility in Munich, Germany, with first production units sold in late 2006.OUR PRODUCT AWARDS Our revolutionary neck brace has won the following awards:Motocross Action: 5/5 star product rating (2007).TW MX: Product of year (2009).RacerX: Product of the decade (2009).Motocross Action: Reader voted decade’s most significant product (2009).Dirt Bike Magazine: Product of the year (2010).Freeride Magazine: Eurobike innovations award (2010).ISPO Brandnew AwardS: Best protection at bike expo (2010).TW MX: GPX Pro – Product of the year (2011).RacerX: Neck protection readers choice award (2012).World of Mountainbike magazine in Germany awards Leatt their “Best of 2016” Award (2016)Share this:FacebookLinkedInGooglePrintEmail     NavigationThe CompanyHomeCompany ProfileMeet the TeamMission and StrategyLeatt HistoryCode of EthicsLeatt ProtectivesThe Leatt BlogLeatt TestimonialsInvestor InfoFilings / FinancialsStock QuotesInvestor RelationsShareholder PresentationShareholder FAQContact UsShareholder Updates: Email Sign-Up  Notices & Disclaimers | © Copyright Leatt Corporation 2008 - 2017 | Design by kri8it.com    Contact informationResident Agent: PMB# 334 2215-B Renaissance Drive Las Vegas NV 89119USA Distribution Office: Two Eleven Distribution LLC 