 FAQ - Leatt Corporation             Leatt Corporation DESIGNERS, DEVELOPERS AND MARKETERS OF INNOVATIVE PROTECTIVE GEAR for sportsLeatt CorporationDESIGNERS, DEVELOPERS AND MARKETERS OF INNOVATIVE PROTECTIVE GEAR for sports     FAQ Archive What is the Company’s strategy to increase shareholder value?Since 2012 the Company has become a fully reporting SEC Company, the shares are now DTC eligible, a reverse split has been effected and management has participated in a US road show to meet potential investors. All these endeavours are aimed at improving shareholder value. Please see our latest press releases at www.leatt-corp.com and 2013 Investors Presentation at http://www.leatt-corp.com/uploads/LeattInvestorPresentation2013.pdf.   What new products does the Company plan to introduce?The Company plans to launch a variety of products this year including new body armour (hard shell and soft-shell protectors), as well as new neck braces. The Company’s research and development team is also working on other products which we expect to introduce in the near term.Please see the Company’s latest press releases on our corporate website at www.leatt-corp.com and 2013 Investors Presentation at http://www.leatt-corp.com/uploads/LeattInvestorPresentation2013.pdf   Where can I buy Leatt products?Please see the Company’s website: http://www.leatt-brace.com/where-to-buyOr visit the online shop (*currently shipping in USA only) at: http://www.leattshop.com/   How many distributors does Leatt have worldwide?The Company sells its products through approximately 60 distributors worldwide. The Company distributes directly to retailers in South Africa through its South African branch and directly to retailers in United States through its subsidiary Two Eleven Distribution, LLC.   Where can I find the current share price of the Company’s stock?Please see http://www.otcmarkets.com/stock/LEAT/quote   Where can I find the Company’s financial information?Please see our Financials section: Click here   How do I make sure the Company has my correct address?Kindly contact the Company’s transfer agent to ensure that they have your current address:Interwest Transfer Company, Inc. 1981 Murray Holladay Road, Suite 100 Salt Lake City, UT 84117 Postal: P.O. Box 17136 Salt Lake City, UT 84117 Phone: (801)272-9294 Fax: (801)277-3147   How do I make my stock certificate ready to sell?You can take/send your certificate to a licensed broker-dealer, who will verify it, perform the necessary due diligence and then digitize the certificate for easy sale when you wish to trade the shares. A licensed broker-dealer or a brokerage firm should be able to assist and advise you. You can check the FINRA database to find a broker in good standing: http://brokercheck.finra.org/Search/Search.aspx   What do I do if I lose my share certificate or damage my share certificate?Kindly contact the Company’s Transfer Agent directly for assistance, their details are as follows: Interwest Transfer Company, Inc. 1981 Murray Holladay Road, Suite 100 Salt Lake City, UT 84117 Postal: P.O. Box 17136 Salt Lake City, UT 84117 Phone: (801)272-9294 Fax: (801)277-3147   I would appreciate it if you could direct me to someone who can help me with advice on what I should do with these shares?A licensed broker-dealer or a brokerage firm should be able to assist and advise you. You can check the FINRA database to find a broker in good standing: http://brokercheck.finra.org/Search/Search.aspx 1 2 Next →   NavigationThe CompanyHomeCompany ProfileMeet the TeamMission and StrategyLeatt HistoryCode of EthicsLeatt ProtectivesThe Leatt BlogLeatt TestimonialsInvestor InfoFilings / FinancialsStock QuotesInvestor RelationsShareholder PresentationShareholder FAQContact UsShareholder Updates: Email Sign-Up  Notices & Disclaimers | © Copyright Leatt Corporation 2008 - 2017 | Design by kri8it.com    Contact informationResident Agent: PMB# 334 2215-B Renaissance Drive Las Vegas NV 89119USA Distribution Office: Two Eleven