			Company Description 


			Leatt Corp. designs, develops, markets and distributes personal protective equipment for participants in all forms of motor sports and leisure activities, including riders of motorcycles, bicycles, snowmobiles, car racing drivers and others. It operates through the Leatt-Brace brand which offers a p...
		


                Leatt Corp. designs, develops, markets and distributes personal protective equipment for participants in all forms of motor sports and leisure activities, including riders of motorcycles, bicycles, snowmobiles, car racing drivers and others. It operates through the Leatt-Brace brand which offers a patented injection molded neck protection system designed to prevent potentially devastating injuries to the cervical spine and neck. The company was founded by Christopher James Leatt on March 11, 2005 and is headquartered in Durbanville, South Africa.
            




